  "text": "We calculated basic hemodynamic parameters in a customized LabVIEW (National Instruments, Austin, TX, USA) environment. Cycle length and waveform features were determined manually. Input impedance spectra were generated as previously described [CITATION_1] (Fig.·1B,C) . We defined TVR as the impedance modulus at 0·Hz, Z 1 as the impedance modulus at the first harmonic, and Z C as the average of the impedance moduli from the third harmonic up to 10·Hz. Global C A was calculated using the area under the pressure waveform as:",
